\subsubsection{A spy or thief acquires an ability unique to his skill.}

A spy may use his photographic memory ability to recall spoken
phrases.  Even if a spy does not know the language us- ed, he can
reproduce the phrases phonetically.  Additionally, when a spy
concentrates for (60 - 5 \x Rank) seconds, he can extend his
range of vision and hearing to (100+ 15 \x Rank])07o of %%-hat
it normally is.

