down.  If the GM's roll is greater than the success percentage, the
thief has fallen in climbing the structure.  To determine the height
at which the thief falls, roll D100.  Round the number off to the
nearest 10\% (a roll of 5 is rounded down), and multiply the height
the thief sought to attain by that percentage.  A thief suffers
([Structure Height in Feet/ 10] Squared) Endurance Points when he
falls.
